  "title": "PROCUREMENT CUM QUANTITY SURVEYOR",
  "description": "<ol>\n  <li>Prepare cost estimates, Bills of Quantities (BOQ), and tender documents for construction projects</li>\n  <li>Conduct quantity surveys to determine material, labor, and time requirements for accurate project costing</li>\n  <li>Manage contract administration, including variations, claims, and final accounts, ensuring compliance with contractual terms</li>\n  <li>Monitor project costs and budgets, providing regular reports and forecasts to management</li>\n  <li>Conduct site measurements and valuations, preparing and submitting progress claims and payments</li>\n  <li>Source, evaluate, and negotiate with suppliers and subcontractors for materials, equipment, and services</li>\n  <li>Prepare and issue purchase orders, monitor delivery schedules, and follow up on outstanding orders</li>\n  <li>Review and analyze supplier performance, pricing, and contracts to secure cost savings</li>\n  <li>Maintain accurate records of purchases, quotations, contracts, and supplier databases</li>\n  <li>Ensure procurement activities comply with company policies, industry standards, and relevant regulations</li>\n  <li>Liaise closely with project managers, site teams, and other internal departments to coordinate purchasing and cost control activities</li>\n  <li>Stay updated on market trends and new products to identify opportunities for cost savings and recommend alternative solutions</li>\n  <li>Assist in resolving discrepancies related to invoices, deliveries, and contractual issues</li>\n</ol>",
  "minimumYearsExperience": 3,
